<exercise checkit-seed="0045" checkit-slug="E3" checkit-title="Solving linear systems">
  <statement>
    <p>Show how to find the solution set for the following 
    
            system of linear equations.
            <md alignment="alignat" alignat-columns=" 5 "><mrow>x_{1} &amp;-&amp; 3 \, x_{2} &amp;-&amp; x_{3} &amp;-&amp; x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 0</mrow><mrow> &amp; &amp;  &amp; &amp; x_{3} &amp;+&amp; 3 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 1</mrow><mrow>-2 \, x_{1} &amp;+&amp; 6 \, x_{2} &amp;+&amp; 4 \, x_{3} &amp;+&amp; 8 \, x_{4} &amp;=&amp; 2</mrow></md></p>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <me>\mathrm{RREF} \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; -1 &amp; -1 &amp; 0 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 3 &amp; 1 \\
-2 &amp; 6 &amp; 4 &amp; 8 &amp; 2
\end{array}\right]  =  \left[\begin{array}{cccc|c}
1 &amp; -3 &amp; 0 &amp; 2 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 3 &amp; 1 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
    <p>The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \, a - 2 \, b + 1 \\
a \\
-3 \, b + 1 \\
b
\end{array}\right] \middle|\,a\text{\texttt{,}}b\in\mathbb{R}\right\} </m></p>
  </answer>
</exercise>

